				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="I've watched this more than any other movie in my life and I have no regrets! https://t.co/2QeGwrdsAT" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 22:01:00 GMT" tweetId="1408183402570911745" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408183402570911745" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="It's also educational! https://t.co/d3KAxpnO1h" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 22:02:56 GMT" tweetId="1408183888162197505" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408183888162197505" inReplyToId="1408183402570911745" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Thread https://t.co/AxBmfcfCD2" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 20:44:36 GMT" tweetId="1408164176569196548" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408164176569196548" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="Recent @gaslitnation episode on Missouri as the bellwether of American decline: https://t.co/lQFoO89SaV" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 20:45:28 GMT" tweetId="1408164392064147461" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408164392064147461" inReplyToId="1408164176569196548" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="A thread on Giuliani's long history with the Trump crime cult https://t.co/fdktR0dK8L" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:22:15 GMT" tweetId="1408098154789146630" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408098154789146630" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="Reminder that the main purpose of Trump's lawyers has never been to practice law. A thread: https://t.co/LaQRJ4k8UX" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:15:36 GMT" tweetId="1408096478338465795" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408096478338465795" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="From 2018: https://t.co/UoYvOEfFUQ" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:17:20 GMT" tweetId="1408096914441228294" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408096914441228294" inReplyToId="1408096478338465795" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
						<outline text="When Giuliani was acting as Trump's &quot;lawyer&quot; during the presidency, he was not actually licensed to practice law in DC. It is good (and long overdue) that he was disbarred in New York. But the actual practice of law was never his main role in this operation." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:18:29 GMT" tweetId="1408097205169360909" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1408097205169360909" inReplyToId="1408096914441228294" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="https://t.co/PAre0tBZlj https://t.co/8GQkVLeEUW" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 15:40:16 GMT" tweetId="1407725199840133131" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407725199840133131" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="Every week @gaslitnation does a bonus episode for our Patreon subscribers! This week we discuss who should replace Merrick Garland as AG and more! Subscribing gives you access to all past and future bonus episodes and keeps our independent show going: https://t.co/Na8D7sa2BC" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 14:47:49 GMT" tweetId="1407712002064191490" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407712002064191490" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="&quot;We need to redefine what bipartisanship means. Bipartisanship means delivering popular policies for people. If 70% of voters support a policy, then it is bipartisan -- regardless whether a Republican in Congress supports it.&quot; - @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:51:13 GMT" tweetId="1407682655718608900" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407682655718608900" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="&quot;Kyrsten Sinema is acting like she's not going to run again. She reminds me of Sarah Palin when Palin left her job to rake in money as a reality TV celebrity. That's why it doesn't matter to her if people can vote.&quot; &amp;lt;--my Sinema theory on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:23:21 GMT" tweetId="1407675645207982081" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407675645207982081" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				<outline text="&quot;The intensity of the GOP to undermine voting rights has not been the surprising part of this. The lack of urgency among the Democrats to combat is the surprising part, esp because the GOP's strategy was obvious in advance.&quot; -- Ari Berman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:11:36 GMT" tweetId="1407672685501497346" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407672685501497346" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="&quot;We are losing critical amounts of time. It's pretty remarkable to me that the Dems couldn't built more support in their caucus. Conversations about the filibuster should have been happening months ago, not starting now.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:13:35 GMT" tweetId="1407673184674009091" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407673184674009091" inReplyToId="1407672685501497346" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
						<outline text="&quot;One of the most striking parallels between today and the Jim Crow era is that the federal government just *gave up* on protecting voting rights. Between 1890 and 1957, Congress did almost nothing to stop voter suppression.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation  https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:27:46 GMT" tweetId="1407676756941848582" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407676756941848582" inReplyToId="1407673184674009091" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
							<outline text="&quot;I'm worried history will repeat itself. Not that we will have poll taxes or literacy tests, but the idea that one party will do everything it can to undermine democracy and there will be no federal response.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:28:53 GMT" tweetId="1407677037146411009" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407677037146411009" inReplyToId="1407676756941848582" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
								<outline text="&quot;I've never met a single person on the street who cared about the filibuster. It's shocking from a pragmatic standpoint that the Democrats would rather keep a vestige of Jim Crow than stop the next wave of Jim Crow laws.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:45:04 GMT" tweetId="1407681107307515906" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407681107307515906" inReplyToId="1407677037146411009" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
									<outline text="&quot;The Dems have valued antiquated institutions and vague notions of bipartisanship over actually delivering for people's lives. It's a complete moral abdication of their responsibility.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:46:56 GMT" tweetId="1407681579489574915" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407681579489574915" inReplyToId="1407681107307515906" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
										<outline text="&quot;No one in 50 years is going to look back and say, 'You know what? We kept the filibuster! The planet is now burning and democracy was on fire, but we kept the filibuster so it was all worth it!'&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:48:43 GMT" tweetId="1407682028053708801" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407682028053708801" inReplyToId="1407681579489574915" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
										</outline>
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&quot;Voter suppression is happening on two related tracks: 1) laws passed making it harder to vote 2) overturning election results altogether. That they're happening at the same time is the most chilling aspect of this.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 11:54:03 GMT" tweetId="1407668270287761414" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407668270287761414" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
					<outline text="&quot;The GOP is doing everything they can to make it harder to vote, if they do not succeed, their fallback option is to simply nullify the will of the voters. I'm not sure they will succeed, but they are learning from 2020.&quot; https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 11:55:37 GMT" tweetId="1407668663885484035" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407668663885484035" inReplyToId="1407668270287761414" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" >
						<outline text="&quot;By 2022, voting rules will be more restrictive in a number of states compared to 2020. The GOP is reducing polling places, drop boxes, absentee ballot forms, mobile voting units, etc.&quot; -- @AriBerman on @gaslitnation https://t.co/fJ7eQQr6xd" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 12:04:49 GMT" tweetId="1407670979858468866" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407670979858468866" inReplyToId="1407668663885484035" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Old thread on how Merrick Garland is actually terrible and why people fell for propaganda saying otherwise https://t.co/cdsmEAxgfU" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 11:18:08 GMT" tweetId="1407659230295900170" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407659230295900170" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 22" type="calendarDay" name="22" >
				<outline text="New @gaslitnation is out! In “Voter Suppression Emergency”, our guest Ari Berman breaks down the legal warfare that is turning the United States into an electoral autocracy. A must-listen in this perilous time! https://t.co/5GfQhWHHgv" type="tweet" created="Wed, 23 Jun 2021 02:31:52 GMT" tweetId="1407526790956978178" urltweet="https://twitter.com/sarahkendzior/status/1407526790956978178" tweetUserName="sarahkendzior" />
